IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROVIDE A GOVERNANCE STRUCTURE THROUGH WHICH THE PARTICIPATING LOCAL ASSOCIATIONS MAY COOPERATIVELY PROVIDE SERVICES FOR THEIR MEMBERS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: ASSIST WISCONSIN EDUCATION ASSOCIATION COUNCIL-AFFILIATED LOCAL ASSOCIATIONS IN COLLECTIVE BARGAINING, MEMBER RIGHTS, PUBLIC RELATIONS, PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT, POLITICAL ACTION, AND OTHER AREAS.
IRS990.Desc: THE OBJECTIVES OF WEAC REGION 6 SHALL BE TO AID TEACHERS AND EDUCATIONAL SUPPORT PROFESSIONALS (ESP) IN OBTAINING IMPROVED WAGES, HOURS AND WORKING CONDITIONS: TO DEVELOP AMONG THE MEMBERSHIP AND THE PUBLIC A BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF THE ISSUES AND PROBLEMS IN THE AREA OF TEACHERS AND ESP RIGHTS; TO ADVANCE THE CIVIL, HUMAN, AND ACADEMIC RIGHTS OF THE MEMBERSHIP; TO PROVIDE FOR THE INVOLVEMENT OF ETHNIC MINORITY MEMBERS IN ASSOCIATION ACTIVITIES; TO PROMOTE THE HUMAN AND CIVIL RIGHTS AND EDUCATIONAL WELFARE OF ALL STUDENTS; TO IMPROVE EDUCATIONAL SYSTEMS IN WEAC REGION 6 BY IMPROVING CURRICULUM AND INSTRUCTION ACTIVITIES; AND TO ENCOURAGE TEACHERS AND ESP TO REGISTER AND VOTE, AND TO EXERCISE THEIR FULL RIGHTS AND RESPONSIBILITIES OF CITIZENSHIP AND TO PARTICIPATE IN THE POLITICAL LIFE OF LOCAL, STATE AND NATIONAL COMMUNITIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MEMBERSHIP IN WEAC REGION 6 SHALL BE LIMITED TO THOSE LOCAL ASSOCIATIONS IN GOOD STANDING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE REPRESENTATIVE ASSEMBLY COMPOSED OF MEMBERS ELECTS THE GOVERNING BODY OF THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AMENDMENTS TO THE CONSTITUTION AND BYLAWS MUST BE RATIFIED BY 2/3 OF THE VOTING MEMBERS OF THE REPRESENTATIVE ASSEMBLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PREPARED FORM 990 IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY A UNISERV DIRECTOR BEFORE THE RETURN IS FILED WITH THE IRS. A COPY OF THE FINAL FORM 990 IS MADE AVAILABLE TO THE ASSOCIATION'S GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: SALARIES AND BENEFITS OF THE UNISERV DIRECTORS ARE DETERMINED AS PART OF A COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AGREEMENT. THE CURRENT COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AGREEMENT EXPIRES IN 2026.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ASSOCIATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST ON A CASE-BY-CASE BASIS.
